The paper deals with computational complexity and solution concepts for weighted voting games, which are typically studied in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of algorithms to compute the nucleolus suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a general framework for computing the nucleolus, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
